    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose wide-field (1300 pc x 440 pc), high-resolution (4.4 pc) observations of the spiral galaxy M83 in the 12CO J=2-1 line.  The proposed field coverage samples the molecular gas from a spiral-arm upstream through the arm into the next inter-arm region in this one of the closest spiral galaxies.  The ALMA Cycle 2 provides the first opportunity for resolving the internal structures of molecular clouds and their evolution during spiral arm passage.  In particular, the development of small clumps -- directly relevant to star formation -- will be revealed for the first time.  Our recent studies of the Milky Way Galaxy have shown such a development of star-forming dense clumps.  The proposed observations of this nearly face-on galaxy permits us to directly correlate the development with the large-scale galactic structure (spiral arm).</prp:abstract>
